column469:
12/Sep/24 10:44 PM;vleung1;Yes, in the example of changing the publish status, this would be considered a high priority import and will go through the same process.
If data on a track has changed and the product has more than 300 tracks, as is in this case, GRAS Export will only process them over the weekend when there is less traffic.

This shouldn't delay other products coming in from GRPS to EOM, unless they are updating the same data. For example, the same participant.  In that case, this will cause a concurrency exception (this can happen at either AOMA or EOM side) and will be redirected to a different queue to reprocess again, one product at a time to avoid the same concurrency exception.  So this will not take up all lanes on the highway.;;;

